c#: Item.GetFirstName()

In this C# expression field, you can specify a custom filter. This filter expression is added to Search Filters which are applied on dataset for this list module.

Tips:

You must use write expression like AddFilter(u=> Your Filter expression on each instance)

======== DEFAULT ================================

M# generates appropriate filter (Except Custom search Element)

======== WHEN TO USE/SET IT? ====================

If the property is persistent in DB and you want add a custom logic filter

======== EXAMPLES ===============================

Filter for email property

if (txtEmail.Text.HasValue())

{

AddFilter(u => u.Email.Contains(txtEmail.Text.Trim(), false));

}

Filter for Postcode property

if (txtPostcode.Text.HasValue())

{

AddFilter(u => u.Postcode = txtEmail.Text.Trim());

}

